args: Wait. I'm detecting a huge\namplification in mana!
HA HA HA HA! Glorious! No matter what\nanyone says, conflict is the essence of\nlife! Conflict is the root of ALL!
I suspect we're about to contend with one\nof the Five Archdemons! Beware!

Yes... Not long now. I am on the cusp of
evolving into a stronger, purer existence.
So let us fight. Let us attempt to murder
each other once more!
Why are you so fixated on violence?
Why? I told you before—it is our nature.\nAll living things must inevitably place\nthemselves in conflict.
▷Don't you push your twisted values on\nus! Not everyone seeks to fight the way\nyou do!◁
Your pathetic pacifism is but a byway to\nindolence and decay.
Wait. Something about her's different now.
The moment they are born, living creatures\nare thrust into a cycle of conflict. The only\nway to survive is to fight, and to win.
That struggle for survival is the very basis\nof evolution. Conversely, to avoid strife is\nto degenerate.
TO FIGHT IS TO LIVE! You do not wish for\nwar? You seek to live in peace? Cast aside\nyour disgusting indolence, you lazy beasts!
I shall steal away your fear, your guilt—\neverything that would snuff out the embers\nof conflict before they begin to blaze!
Sadness, anger... We can't anticipate\nher movements when her emotions are\nfluctuating this wildly!
Come all and revel in the spiral of strife!\nIt will be the fulcrum of your evolution.
Hah. You practice that speech in a mirror\nor something, psycho?

It's true that conflict IS necessary at times.
Like when you have to protect something
you're not willing to lose, or when you
need to knock a villain down a few pegs.

And yeah, in some ways, our struggles ARE
what make us stronger. But your take on
the subject is so short-sighted it's almost
hilarious—y'know, if it wasn't so horrific.
People need to have emotions to process\nthe significance of the battles they fight.\nTHAT is what leads to evolution.
Your hedonistic views on what constitutes\ngrowth are superficial at best, demon.
Absurd. All of you are as absurd as you are\npathetic. Thrash as you will—I shall drag\nyou all into the abyss of strife by FORCE!
